metadata.name: Pushing Through The Voices of Doubt
metadata.description:
You will never make it  
You bring shame to your family 
You are worthless  
You are pathetic  
You are a burden  
You are not a real artist  
Give up 

For years, these thoughts plagued my mind. They pulled me into a miserable existence and controlled every fibre of my being. I wasted so much time buried in misery because I didn’t know how to be anything else.

Every damn day, for years on end, looking at life through a dark mirror. 
And yet, after all that, all the self-loathing and suffering, 

I’m still here.
